Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat(persistence):=20durable=20server=20state?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20=E2=80=94=20the=20root=20cause=20of=20'everything=20broke'?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Diagnosis, proven by executing the built artifacts: content.js in a
simulated DOM (pins+pill render, composer works, pin_add fires
correctly) and background.js against a live server (websocket connects,
writes complete). Every layer was functional — the failure was
environmental: tsx watch restarts on every file change and state was
purely in-memory, so every applied patch wiped all communities,
connections, and boards before testing.

Fix: communities (incl. boards/pins/highlights/votes), connections,
blocks, presence masks snapshot to disk every 2s + on SIGINT/SIGTERM,
restored on boot. Verified with a real kill/restart cycle. Deliberately
NOT persisted: chat messages (zero-retention), sessions, cursors.
TABCOM_STATE_FILE overrides location (default data/, gitignored);
TABCOM_EPHEMERAL=1 disables (tests use it).

Also: pin/cursor coordinates guarded against zero-width documents.
